      }), "\nThe Tray with design of snake is a unique and intricately decorated calabash, crafted from a gourd. It holds a special place in the Lydia Luhman Pederson collection as it was not collected by Lydia herself; it was instead her niece Sonjia Ulstad – the donor of the Pederson collection – who acquired it during her 1967 voyage to Nigeria. The art of calabash carving and decoration as seen here is a prevalent form of expression in Nigeria. With their outer parts removed, gourds are skillfully carved to create designs ranging from abstract patterns to animal shapes. These gourds are often dyed in vibrant colors such as red or black."]
